I was recommended by a church member to try out Manners, so I did, never again I wanted to order food for Christmas so I called them and asked if I wanted food for Christmas how far in advance did I have to place the order I spoke with Abdul and he said the day before if its not a large order. I came to Manners on Saturday Morning(Christmas eve) placed my order a large Lasagna, small Rice and beans, and Peach Cobbler. I go Sunday afternoon(Christmas day) to pick up the order, I waited for about half hour then Innis comes and tells me "we don't have any peach cobbler" I said don't you make it here? he replied yes then how you don't have any, ok I ask for my money back he asked did I want banana pudding... No I wanted peach cobbler. then he goes back and comes back with the rest of the things I ordered on a rolling cart another man loaded into my car as he is putting it in my car I notice the trays are the same size I question are those both half size trays the man answered yes I said well I ordered a full lasagna and a half peas and rice again I go back in the restaurant and approach Innis and say to him my receipt says full lasagna and you gave me half, he looks at me puzzled I asked do you have another half in the back to make 2 halves a full he replied no we don't do I want to pick something else, I said you guys came highly recommended and you cant even get my small order correct, just give me back the money for the lasagna then I left. I will never order or recommend anyone to your establishment and the lasagna wasn't good at all it was just one flat layer and you charge so much money........ Signed: Highly Disappointed!!!!!!
